The '''Dutch Automated Vehicle Initiative (DAVI)''' is a research and demonstration initiative developing [[autonomous car|automated vehicle]]s for use on public roads.

The project is special in that, besides simply making driverless cars, it also focuses on having the automated vehicles share information amongst each other.<ref>http://davi.connekt.nl/about_davi/</ref> The aim is to have the cars helping to avoid traffic congestion, by reducing the safety distance between the cars (from 2 seconds drive distance now to just 0.5 seconds) and avoiding sudden traffic slow-downs (due to manoeuvres undertaken by drivers).

